de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.data

Interface NumberVector

  • All Superinterfaces:
    FeatureVector<Number>, SpatialComparable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SparseNumberVector
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractNumberVector, BitVector, ByteVector, Centroid, DeLiCluLeafEntry, DoubleVector, FloatVector, IntegerVector, OneDimensionalDoubleVector, ProjectedCentroid, RdKNNLeafEntry, ShortVector, SparseByteVector, SparseDoubleVector, SparseFloatVector, SparseIntegerVector, SparseShortVector, SpatialPointLeafEntry, Vector

    public interface NumberVector
extends FeatureVector<Number>, SpatialComparable
    Interface NumberVector defines the methods that should be implemented by any Object that is element of a real vector space of type N.
    Author:
    Arthur Zimek
